What do you want,
Frank?

00:16:32,725 --> 00:16:35,627
Guess who's the new head
of the Sanitation Department.

00:16:35,761 --> 00:16:38,831
I don't know.
John fucking Rizzo.

00:16:38,964 --> 00:16:40,933
[CHUCKLES]

00:16:41,066 --> 00:16:42,001
Jesus.

00:16:43,268 --> 00:16:46,872
Rizzo hates your guts.
No shit? Maybe that's why

00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:51,577
I can't get any city business.
Do you blame him? He's scared.

00:16:51,710 --> 00:16:53,312
I'm scared myself.

00:16:53,445 --> 00:16:55,381
Hey, Pop ran a different
kind of business.

00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:57,316
Can we move into
the 20th century here?

00:16:57,449 --> 00:16:59,351
I can't talk to Rizzo,
you can.

00:16:59,485 --> 00:17:00,919
I gave you my share
of the business.

00:17:01,053 --> 00:17:02,755
Garbage ain't what
it used to be, Carmine.

00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:04,857
Yeah? How much
can it change, huh?

00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:05,924
What about you?

00:17:07,192 --> 00:17:08,527
You live in a dump like this?

00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:10,529
At least I don't
have to hurt people.

00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:12,164
Who's talking about
hurting anybody?

00:17:12,297 --> 00:17:14,500
I'm talking about
coming home, huh?

00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:16,068
I'm talking about family.

00:17:20,105 --> 00:17:21,206
CARMINE:
Family.

00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:24,009
Five years ago,
he steals my wife,

00:17:24,143 --> 00:17:27,179
and now he talks to me
about family.

00:17:27,312 --> 00:17:28,747
I'm in Vegas on business.

00:17:30,482 --> 00:17:32,151
In two weeks,
we go home together.

00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:34,553
And if I don't?

00:17:41,326 --> 00:17:43,729
HARVEY:
I don't get it. I don't
understand it. Help me out here.

00:17:43,862 --> 00:17:46,198
This guy is ruining my dream.
Would you relax?

00:17:46,331 --> 00:17:48,467
You're gonna have a stroke.
He hustles old women!

00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,635
You hustle golf.

00:17:49,768 --> 00:17:53,272
He fucked Mom!
He helped with the funeral.

00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:56,608
She cut us out
of the will!

00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:58,410
[GRUNTS]
Oh, God.

00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:02,247
[GASPS]

00:18:02,381 --> 00:18:04,283
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey.

00:18:05,617 --> 00:18:08,087
I'll let the lawyers
get it all

00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:10,255
before I bend over
and let that scumbag

00:18:10,389 --> 00:18:11,757
make a mockery
of my dream.

00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:13,559
[FLAMES CRACKLING]
Fire!

00:18:14,726 --> 00:18:16,128
Fire!

00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,196
Max!

00:18:17,663 --> 00:18:18,530
Max!

00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:20,332
[MUTTERING]

00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,501
Max, are you here?

00:18:25,637 --> 00:18:26,905
He's not here, thank God.

00:18:30,909 --> 00:18:32,845
[♪♪♪]

00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,084
Come on, come on.

00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:42,387
Damn it.

00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,266
[GRUNTS]

00:18:54,399 --> 00:18:55,968
[METAL CREAKING]

00:19:04,877 --> 00:19:06,178
Quite a bonfire, Dad.

00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,246
Max.

00:19:07,746 --> 00:19:09,014
Oh!

00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:11,950
God. Where have you been?
I was at Phyllis', all right?

00:19:15,954 --> 00:19:17,756
Is that everything we own?

00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,091
CARMINE:
Yeah.

00:19:19,224 --> 00:19:21,960
Great.
I'm going back to sleep.

00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:26,131
Crispy Critters, huh?

00:19:30,536 --> 00:19:32,504
Tough break, Carmine.
Yeah.

00:19:34,273 --> 00:19:35,207
Are you insured?

00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:37,442
Get out of here, Mike.

00:19:39,144 --> 00:19:40,445
It's not insured, babe.

00:19:47,653 --> 00:19:48,654
Are you all right?

00:19:49,755 --> 00:19:50,689
Yeah.

00:19:51,823 --> 00:19:52,791
Yeah, thanks.

00:19:56,161 --> 00:19:58,130
Carmine.
Huh?

00:19:58,263 --> 00:20:00,532
Do you have a place
to sleep, sweetheart?

00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:01,967
Yeah, Grace.

00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,035
Thank you.

00:20:04,102 --> 00:20:06,038
[SIREN WAILING
IN THE DISTIANCE]

00:20:20,452 --> 00:20:22,387
[♪♪♪]

00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:39,338
[COUGHS]

00:20:49,147 --> 00:20:52,117
What's up? Okay, okay,
I'll tell you what's up.

00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:56,688
Harvey wants to plow under our
place and build Little Vegas.

00:20:58,190 --> 00:21:00,559
I know, I know,
I need somebody, Syl,

00:21:00,692 --> 00:21:03,061
but you can't find
those type people

00:21:03,195 --> 00:21:04,830
by looking
in the Yellow Pages.

00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:22,514
CARMINE:
You kick me again, Sam,

00:21:22,648 --> 00:21:25,017
I'm gonna feed you that shoe
for breakfast.

00:21:25,150 --> 00:21:27,419
I hear Mutt and Jeff
paid you a visit last night.

00:21:27,552 --> 00:21:28,654
Harvey's a weasel.

00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:31,123
He does, however,
have good taste in lawyers.

00:21:31,256 --> 00:21:32,291
Yeah, tell me about it.

00:21:32,424 --> 00:21:34,493
[SPEAKS IN YIDDISH]

00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:35,894
You've lost already.

00:21:37,696 --> 00:21:38,997
You owe me for the trailer.

00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:41,600
You ought to pay me for
putting it out of its misery.

00:21:41,733 --> 00:21:45,070
SAM:
Right, so clean up,
come over and see me.

00:21:45,203 --> 00:21:46,972
[GLASS CRUNCHES]

00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:55,681
Nu?

00:21:56,782 --> 00:21:58,950
Carmine, my boy.

00:21:59,084 --> 00:22:00,819
Want a cocktail?

00:22:00,952 --> 00:22:04,156
It's 8:30 in the morning.
It's at least 5:00 in China.

00:22:04,289 --> 00:22:08,493
Yeah, what do you want?
Come, take a walk with me.

00:22:15,233 --> 00:22:19,171
SAM:
Sylvia, Martha, my partner
Saul and I came out here

00:22:19,304 --> 00:22:21,740
when Vegas was just
a dream of Bugsy Siegel

00:22:21,873 --> 00:22:23,675
and other now deceased Jews.

00:22:23,809 --> 00:22:25,977
Long before you
olive oil types ruined it.

00:22:26,111 --> 00:22:27,946
CARMINE:
Sam had dug himself
a deep hole.

00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:29,715
The only way out
was to pull a scam,

00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,116
but he needed an accomplice.

00:22:31,249 --> 00:22:33,452
Someone to blame
if things went sour.

00:22:33,585 --> 00:22:36,088
In the old days,
he used Martha's husband.

00:22:37,222 --> 00:22:39,591
Now he was trying to use me.

00:22:39,725 --> 00:22:43,228
When you look out over that
trailer park, what do you see?

00:22:43,362 --> 00:22:47,566
A godforsaken shithole.
All right, fair enough.

00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,901
Now he thinks he's the
reincarnation of Bugsy Siegel.

00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,269
Who?
Harvey Brandstein.

00:22:51,403 --> 00:22:52,337
Oh, God.

00:22:52,471 --> 00:22:54,306
I sold him the land
for the golf course.

00:22:54,439 --> 00:22:56,408
Like a yutz, I also
sold him the option

00:22:56,541 --> 00:22:57,976
to everything
you see out there,

00:22:58,110 --> 00:23:00,479
the spa, my home,
my life.

00:23:00,612 --> 00:23:02,381
The option lasts till
the end of the month,

00:23:02,514 --> 00:23:03,849
less than two weeks
from now.

00:23:03,982 --> 00:23:07,953
His dream is to rip down my
eyesore and build Little Vegas.

00:23:08,086 --> 00:23:09,154
Little Vegas?

00:23:09,287 --> 00:23:12,090
A bigger, much more
impressive eyesore.

00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:14,860
Well, what's he gonna use
to purchase Little Vegas with?

00:23:14,993 --> 00:23:16,495
Mafia moolah, Carmine.

00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:19,664
The family. You are familiar
with the family, are you not?

00:23:19,798 --> 00:23:21,233
You want me
to get him the loan?

00:23:21,366 --> 00:23:23,101
No, you stupid putz.
Goodbye.

00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:27,205
Sorry. I want you to make sure
he never sees that loan.

00:23:27,339 --> 00:23:28,573
I'd like to help you,

00:23:28,707 --> 00:23:30,342
but I'm not exactly
the first person

00:23:30,475 --> 00:23:32,577
that la famiglia
checks with

00:23:32,711 --> 00:23:34,112
when looking to purchase
real estate.

00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,781
I didn't say
it was gonna be easy,

00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:37,549
I can give you money
if you help me.

00:23:37,682 --> 00:23:39,251
You're a real
Donald Trump.

00:23:39,384 --> 00:23:41,987
I could maybe scrape together
about 25, 30G's.

00:23:43,555 --> 00:23:44,756
I don't think so.

00:23:44,890 --> 00:23:47,092
He's looking for 190G's
option money

00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:48,760
to keep
his big dream alive.

00:23:48,894 --> 00:23:50,796
He's dead
without that loan.

00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,470
Look, Carmine, if he
picks up this property,

00:23:58,603 --> 00:24:00,872
I have life in a nursing home
to look forward to.

00:24:01,006 --> 00:24:02,641
I'm not talking about
homicide here.

00:24:02,774 --> 00:24:04,643
All we have to do
is stall him till the 1st,

00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:07,279
then he has no right to pull
this place out from under me.

00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:10,816
What do you think?

00:24:14,052 --> 00:24:15,821
I think
I wanna think about it.

00:24:18,023 --> 00:24:20,325
So who's gonna fuck me next?

00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:21,927
I mean, Sam wasn't
the most honest guy

00:24:22,060 --> 00:24:25,096
to go into business with.
Who is?

00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:27,999
But Harvey torched my trailer.

00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:34,072
Still, using my family name to
stall Harvey was a stupid move,

00:24:34,206 --> 00:24:36,374
and potentially suicidal.

00:24:36,508 --> 00:24:38,944
You see, Sam and my brother
are both hoods.

00:24:39,077 --> 00:24:42,481
The only difference is
Sam's not a pro,

00:24:42,614 --> 00:24:45,183
which means that I
could never count on Sam

00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:46,618
to stand up for me,

00:24:46,751 --> 00:24:48,820
but I could count on my brother
to kill me.

00:24:49,754 --> 00:24:50,689
Shit.

00:24:51,857 --> 00:24:53,191
Why do I keep making
the same mistakes

00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:55,327
over and over and over again?

00:24:56,862 --> 00:24:58,163
Oh, Gargoyle?

00:24:59,898 --> 00:25:00,999
Do you realize
in a few years

00:25:01,132 --> 00:25:03,034
we'll never be able to pull
this shit off?

00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,271
Ketchup, please.

00:25:08,039 --> 00:25:11,309
MAN [OVER PA]:
Phil to the pro shack.
Phil to the pro shack.

00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:13,945
Take the governor
off that baby, it'll fly.

00:25:15,347 --> 00:25:18,116
Totally power it, maybe
kamikaze into the tree.

00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:19,217
Kamikaze?

00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:23,321
You kids must do all right
selling those golf balls.

00:25:23,455 --> 00:25:24,422
Hi, Harvey.

00:25:24,556 --> 00:25:25,957
You've got some
Swedish meatballs,

00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:27,726
a little pasta,
it looks good.

00:25:27,859 --> 00:25:29,961
What are you two outlaws
up to today?

00:25:30,095 --> 00:25:31,930
Not much.
How about yourself?

00:25:32,063 --> 00:25:35,033
Still teaching these fucking
retards how to hit a golf ball.

00:25:35,166 --> 00:25:38,236
Sounds like a pain.
Oh, I don't mind.

00:25:38,370 --> 00:25:40,639
It's all part of owning
a successful operation.

00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:45,210
What I do mind is,
well, you know.

00:25:45,343 --> 00:25:46,344
What?

00:25:46,478 --> 00:25:48,780
Keeping you from selling
used golf balls

00:25:48,914 --> 00:25:50,782
within chipping distance
of the pro shop.

00:25:50,916 --> 00:25:52,851
Used golf balls
for a buck fifty apiece

00:25:52,984 --> 00:25:54,486
with little
help-me-I'm-a-starving-child

00:25:54,619 --> 00:25:55,754
looks on your faces,

00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:59,424
while inside, inside
I sell new ones for 250.

00:25:59,558 --> 00:26:01,326
But it's a different story

00:26:01,459 --> 00:26:05,664
when you sign the lunch check
"Mr. Gilligan and Mrs. Howell."

00:26:07,465 --> 00:26:10,402
I start to feel like somebody's
making me out to be an idiot.

00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:12,637
A dipshit.

00:26:14,105 --> 00:26:15,040
A douchebag.

00:26:16,641 --> 00:26:19,477
I don't pay myself a big salary
to be a douchebag.

00:26:22,347 --> 00:26:23,949
Well,
don't stop eating.

00:26:24,082 --> 00:26:25,717
I want you to finish it,
enjoy it.

00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:29,788
I'll just...take these

00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:31,256
and do this.
Ow!

00:26:31,389 --> 00:26:33,892
If it happens again,
you'll be two sorry castaways.

00:26:34,025 --> 00:26:34,960
Shit.

00:26:36,127 --> 00:26:37,996
You okay, Max?

00:26:38,129 --> 00:26:39,497
I hate that guy.

00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:44,869
[♪♪♪]

00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:54,412
I think
that's it.

00:26:56,014 --> 00:26:57,649
Kamikaze.
What?

00:26:57,782 --> 00:26:59,351
The tree!
Hit the tree!

00:26:59,484 --> 00:27:00,652
You've gotta be
crazy.

00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:02,053
If I were driving,
I'd hit the tree.

00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:03,855
And we'd be dead.
So?

00:27:06,825 --> 00:27:08,526
MIKE:
Max is a good kid.

00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:11,796
Take an AK-47 to get him
to say anything bad about you.

00:27:11,930 --> 00:27:14,799
P.J. and I was just saying
sometimes it's hard to tell

00:27:14,933 --> 00:27:16,768
who's the parent
and who's the kid here.

00:27:16,901 --> 00:27:18,737
Yeah, I am, Mike.
I'm the parent.

00:27:20,438 --> 00:27:24,042
Look, Carmine, I know this
is none of my business, but...

00:27:24,175 --> 00:27:26,378
Max has been staying over
at our house

00:27:26,511 --> 00:27:29,714
and, uh, what's gonna happen
if you don't get that money?

00:27:31,483 --> 00:27:34,119
You're right, Mike.
It is none of your business.

00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:36,955
I'll get the money,
and you'll be reimbursed

00:27:37,088 --> 00:27:40,091
for every Twinkie that Max
ever lifted from your cupboard.

00:27:40,225 --> 00:27:44,496
P.J. and I feel that
if it comes down to it,

00:27:44,629 --> 00:27:45,930
we're ready to take him in.

00:27:46,064 --> 00:27:48,667
Yeah? Why?
Because we like him.

00:27:50,802 --> 00:27:54,005
That's his job, Mike, to make
sure everybody likes him.

00:27:54,139 --> 00:27:55,240
Don't be fooled by
the fact

00:27:55,373 --> 00:27:57,142
that he's young, healthy,
good-looking,

00:27:57,275 --> 00:27:58,510
kindhearted
and intelligent.

00:27:58,643 --> 00:28:00,745
We're just worried.
Yeah, well, don't.

00:28:07,018 --> 00:28:09,554
Did you hear they dropped
the price on propane again?

00:28:11,156 --> 00:28:12,090
No kidding?

00:28:14,592 --> 00:28:17,696
Listen, do me a favor,

00:28:17,829 --> 00:28:20,198
if you see Einstein,
will you send him home?

00:28:20,331 --> 00:28:21,399
Sure.

00:28:31,576 --> 00:28:33,511
[♪♪♪]

00:28:58,403 --> 00:28:59,771
[GRUNTS]

00:29:09,814 --> 00:29:11,750
[♪♪♪]

00:30:45,810 --> 00:30:46,744
[KNOCKS]

00:30:56,421 --> 00:30:57,655
[KNOCKS]

00:31:19,611 --> 00:31:20,778
Windows.

00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:22,280
Windows?

00:31:23,414 --> 00:31:25,049
My father was
a traveling salesman.

00:31:25,183 --> 00:31:28,553
He used to sit up nights
talking about how to sell.

00:31:28,686 --> 00:31:31,623
The thing they talked about
most was how to read a window.

00:31:31,756 --> 00:31:33,224
If you wanted
someone to buy,

00:31:33,358 --> 00:31:35,994
all you had to do was wait for
that right window to open up,

00:31:36,127 --> 00:31:38,196
and if you were patient,
it would.

00:31:38,329 --> 00:31:41,799
When it did, you'd stick
a bit of yourself in,

00:31:41,933 --> 00:31:43,434
you could sell them
the world.

00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:50,675
It's just a complex.

00:31:50,808 --> 00:31:52,477
I've done all right
in real estate.

00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:55,446
So how is your dad?

00:31:56,381 --> 00:31:57,315
Dead.

00:32:13,765 --> 00:32:14,632
I don't know.

00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,901
Not right now.
Okay, okay.

00:32:18,469 --> 00:32:19,370
[SIGHS]

00:32:19,504 --> 00:32:21,172
Thanks for dinner.
Sure.

00:32:24,842 --> 00:32:25,877
[ENGINE STARTS]

00:32:26,778 --> 00:32:28,079
Watch that
speed limit.

00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:30,148
You bet.

00:32:36,587 --> 00:32:38,523
No, no, Joey,

00:32:38,656 --> 00:32:41,926
Joey, it's more like
Frankie Five Fingers these days.

00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,896
Yeah. Yeah. Huh?

00:32:45,029 --> 00:32:48,399
I'm eating a lot of carrots to
make up for my loss of sight.

00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:49,667
[CHUCKLES]

00:32:49,801 --> 00:32:50,768
Yeah.

00:32:50,902 --> 00:32:54,372
Yeah, well--
Yeah, that's right, Joe.

00:32:54,505 --> 00:32:55,974
Yeah, that's why I called.

00:32:57,175 --> 00:32:58,509
Yeah, listen,

00:32:58,643 --> 00:33:02,413
hey, uh, ahem, I'm gonna be
flush in a couple of weeks,

00:33:02,547 --> 00:33:05,016
but I need about
five or six bills to cover me

00:33:05,149 --> 00:33:08,152
so I can get some
legal representation-- Hey!

00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:10,488
Ow! Chrissake!

00:33:10,621 --> 00:33:12,256
You made me swallow my gum,
damn it.

00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:14,592
Sounded like a desperate phone
call from a desperate man.

00:33:14,726 --> 00:33:15,927
That was
a long-distance call.

00:33:16,060 --> 00:33:18,429
Long distance is expensive,
you already owe me 100.

00:33:18,563 --> 00:33:19,931
I was trying to get it.

00:33:20,064 --> 00:33:22,600
You were the one that wanted
to play 10 bucks a hole.

00:33:22,734 --> 00:33:25,036
Well, I had a bad day,
what can I tell you?

00:33:25,169 --> 00:33:28,373
How about if we play tomorrow?
Double or nothing.

00:33:28,506 --> 00:33:31,309
Come on, Cecil, take a chance.
Columbus did.

00:33:33,745 --> 00:33:35,179
Okay.

00:33:35,313 --> 00:33:36,781
But if you don't win,

00:33:36,914 --> 00:33:39,384
I might be the next one
to burn down your domicile.

