00:33:51,129 --> 00:33:54,032
Do you want a nice cocktail
to go with that ice, Carmine?

00:33:56,167 --> 00:33:57,602
You don't drink,
Grace.

00:33:57,735 --> 00:34:00,772
A girl's gotta start sometime.
I need you, Carmine.

00:34:00,905 --> 00:34:02,940
I've got business
I have to take care of.

00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:06,911
Look, Carmine, I'm really ready
and I'm really ready to pay.

00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:07,912
Grace?

00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:09,380
Really ready.

00:34:09,514 --> 00:34:12,150
I sell mobile homes.
I don't do that anymore.

00:34:12,283 --> 00:34:13,985
Martha's dead,
she'd never know.

00:34:14,118 --> 00:34:15,686
It's got nothing to do
with Martha.

00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,055
For 200 bucks?

00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:24,495
No, I can't do it. Nope.

00:34:31,702 --> 00:34:33,237
[♪♪♪]

00:34:33,371 --> 00:34:34,439
It's all I ever drink.

00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:36,207
CARMINE:
Sam never got over the guilt

00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:37,909
of cheating Martha's husband.

00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:41,079
But I happen to know
from personal experience,

00:34:41,212 --> 00:34:42,647
that guilt doesn't stop a guy

00:34:42,780 --> 00:34:44,982
from making
the same mistake twice.

00:34:45,116 --> 00:34:47,852
I would have never fucked you,
Saul, you know that.

00:34:47,985 --> 00:34:49,720
But when you have to weigh
what's good

00:34:49,854 --> 00:34:52,390
for three other people
on your own scale,

00:34:52,523 --> 00:34:54,892
it can be a heavy burden.

00:34:55,026 --> 00:34:57,962
All right, have a little
swallow, so I don't drink so...

00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:00,398
Sam, come on.
Don't argue, Saul.

00:35:01,532 --> 00:35:03,134
Both of us will feel better.

00:35:32,163 --> 00:35:33,097
[BOTTLE THUDS]

00:35:43,274 --> 00:35:44,375
Uh, hello.

00:35:45,743 --> 00:35:47,011
Look, I hope
you don't mind.

00:35:47,145 --> 00:35:49,447
Max and I
needed a place to live.

00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:51,582
I mean, after my joint
burnt down, I...

00:35:51,716 --> 00:35:54,785
I just-- I haven't looked
inside since I moved away.

00:35:56,287 --> 00:35:57,555
When did you go away, huh?

00:35:58,789 --> 00:36:00,057
When I was 16,

00:36:00,191 --> 00:36:01,893
as far as I got was Vegas.
Yeah.

00:36:02,026 --> 00:36:03,961
It must have been
quite an education.

00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:06,697
No. At the time, I thought
I knew everything anyway.

00:36:08,699 --> 00:36:10,134
I wanted to say thank you...

00:36:11,736 --> 00:36:13,404
for helping with
my mother's funeral.

00:36:13,538 --> 00:36:14,839
My brother should've helped.

00:36:14,972 --> 00:36:18,910
Yeah, well, your brother's a...
An asshole. I know.

00:36:19,043 --> 00:36:22,246
Yeah, well, you know,
it happened so suddenly. I...

00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:23,915
I lost touch
with my mother.

00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:25,183
[SCREEN DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

00:36:25,316 --> 00:36:27,552
No, you know, she talked
about you a lot.

00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:29,754
[SCREEN DOOR CREAKS CLOSED]
[SAM MUTTERS]

00:36:29,887 --> 00:36:31,822
[SAM SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

00:36:33,391 --> 00:36:35,293
He double-crossed
his best friend.

00:36:35,426 --> 00:36:36,794
My father.

00:36:36,928 --> 00:36:37,862
Yeah.

00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:40,765
My mother told you?

00:36:40,898 --> 00:36:44,068
No, I read it in her diary.
You what?

00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,103
[CHUCKLES]
You read my mother's diary?

00:36:46,237 --> 00:36:49,507
Look, it gets slow out here
in the middle of nowhere.

00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,409
I-I mean,
your mother never said,

00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:54,879
"If I should happen to die,
please don't read my diary."

00:36:55,012 --> 00:36:58,516
Well, then,
you're a weird guy, Carmine.

00:36:58,649 --> 00:37:01,185
Yeah, well, I--
I've been called worse.

00:37:01,319 --> 00:37:05,389
[SAM SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:10,828
[SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

00:37:10,962 --> 00:37:13,130
He thought Bugsy Siegel
was a saint.

00:37:13,264 --> 00:37:14,532
You were a Girl Scout?

00:37:14,665 --> 00:37:16,400
I spent my life
in garbage collection.

00:37:16,534 --> 00:37:19,403
Oh, I'm sorry. Garbage
collection in New Jersey.

00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:21,772
I know people who have
been convicted for less.

00:37:22,873 --> 00:37:23,808
Hey, Lexie?

00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:29,680
You wanna go out
for a cup of coffee?

00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:33,684
Yeah, okay.

00:37:35,152 --> 00:37:36,754
We used to hang out
in our trailer.

00:37:36,887 --> 00:37:38,656
Really?
Yeah. She'd be baking.

00:37:38,789 --> 00:37:40,858
Grace?
Big cakes, cookies.

00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:42,793
It was 120 degrees
to begin with.

00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:44,195
Heh! Oh, my God.

00:37:44,328 --> 00:37:46,430
She'd slip us beers
and make us sit

00:37:46,564 --> 00:37:49,066
and listen to stories of Vegas
in the good old days.

00:37:50,368 --> 00:37:52,436
Yeah, it was a great place
to grow up.

00:37:52,570 --> 00:37:53,704
I'll bet.

00:37:53,838 --> 00:37:55,206
How did you end up here?

00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,377
Oh, never
really liked doing

00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:02,613
what I was doing
back in Jersey.

00:38:02,747 --> 00:38:03,681
Which was?

00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:06,217
Garbage collection.

00:38:06,917 --> 00:38:07,852
Right.

00:38:09,220 --> 00:38:11,155
You see, I used to come out
here every once in a while,

00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:12,523
on business.

00:38:12,657 --> 00:38:15,660
Vegas is the only place I knew
besides where I grew up.

00:38:16,694 --> 00:38:18,162
Did you like
where you grew up?

00:38:19,563 --> 00:38:22,500
Well, I don't think where you
grow up matters all that much.

00:38:22,633 --> 00:38:23,567
What matters?

00:38:24,669 --> 00:38:25,603
Your family.

00:38:27,171 --> 00:38:28,773
The people you grew up with.

00:38:31,876 --> 00:38:33,577
I thought I knew
what a family was.

00:38:35,046 --> 00:38:38,249
Yeah, I think about that a lot,
and with a kid.

00:38:38,382 --> 00:38:39,483
Exactly.

00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:42,420
You see, I didn't want Max
to grow up doing...

00:38:42,553 --> 00:38:43,721
garbage collection.

00:38:45,056 --> 00:38:46,357
Do you like it here?

00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:47,825
Well, I'd like it
a lot better

00:38:47,958 --> 00:38:50,461
if I could get on my feet...

00:38:50,594 --> 00:38:52,830
Get out of you own way?
Exactly.

00:38:54,198 --> 00:38:55,132
Exactly.

00:39:03,474 --> 00:39:05,042
Oh, man, I missed the boat.

00:39:07,044 --> 00:39:09,146
I missed the boat
on the big family reunion.

00:39:10,414 --> 00:39:12,650
You were an important part
of her life.

00:39:14,285 --> 00:39:15,886
Yeah.

00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:17,922
I just thought,
someday I would come back

00:39:18,055 --> 00:39:20,157
and my mother and I would
straighten everything out.

00:39:21,592 --> 00:39:23,327
I was so mad when I left.

00:39:24,995 --> 00:39:27,398
You were 16 years old,
right?

00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:29,467
That's what
16-year-old girls are.

00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:33,070
Well, I'm not 16 anymore,
am I?

00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:44,448
Listen, Lex...

00:39:46,751 --> 00:39:50,054
I appreciate you being
so nice considering I...

00:39:50,187 --> 00:39:51,389
Slept with my mother?

00:39:53,624 --> 00:39:55,393
Right.
Sure.

00:39:56,794 --> 00:39:59,463
Good night, Carmine.
Good night, Lexie.

00:40:08,806 --> 00:40:10,574
[CHUCKLES]

00:40:46,544 --> 00:40:48,479
[♪♪♪]

00:41:04,462 --> 00:41:08,432
You don't understand him,
Martha. He's an angry man.

00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:11,135
He'd kill me if he thought
I was standing in the way

00:41:11,268 --> 00:41:12,703
of a city contract.

00:41:12,837 --> 00:41:15,005
He'd murder
his own brother?

00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:16,640
Apparently,
you're not acquainted

00:41:16,774 --> 00:41:19,710
with what he's already done
to much better friends. Cheers.

00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:23,948
How are you gonna fix
what he's done to you?

00:41:24,081 --> 00:41:26,250
Either I fix him,
or he fixes me.

00:41:26,383 --> 00:41:27,985
That's anger talking to anger.

00:41:28,118 --> 00:41:29,820
No, that's me
talking to my brother.

00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:30,888
Do you love him?

00:41:32,356 --> 00:41:33,891
Well, I suppose.

00:41:34,024 --> 00:41:36,994
I don't know, sure, yeah.
Some distant, hateful way.

00:41:38,262 --> 00:41:39,930
Then forgive him.

00:41:40,064 --> 00:41:41,932
What?
Forgive him.

00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:16,634
[CAR APPROACHING]

00:42:24,408 --> 00:42:26,710
Hey, Carmine, que fa?

00:42:26,844 --> 00:42:28,045
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:31,582
Nice place
you got here.

00:42:31,715 --> 00:42:34,685
Oh, the Japanese garden,
that is a very nice touch.

00:42:34,818 --> 00:42:37,521
[SPEAKING GIBBERISH]

00:42:37,655 --> 00:42:39,957
What do you use for fertilizer?
Jimmy Hoffa?

00:42:40,090 --> 00:42:41,659
CARMINE:
You guys want some coffee?

00:42:41,792 --> 00:42:43,093
Yeah, you got some?

00:42:43,227 --> 00:42:45,896
Bobby, why don't you go inside,
take a dump or something.

00:42:50,935 --> 00:42:53,737
So Johnny Rizzo
sends you his best.

00:42:53,871 --> 00:42:55,306
What's that supposed to mean?

00:42:55,439 --> 00:42:57,074
It means
he didn't send me his best.

00:42:57,207 --> 00:42:58,842
I can't get through
to that stugots.

00:42:58,976 --> 00:43:03,347
Frank...guys don't forget
when you pin 'em down,

00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:06,550
wait till they scream,
and spit down their throat.

00:43:06,684 --> 00:43:07,918
Well,
that was 30 years ago.

00:43:08,052 --> 00:43:10,721
Well, I still remember
every time you did it to me.

00:43:10,854 --> 00:43:13,591
But you thought you were just
some kid being an asshole.

00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:15,459
Yeah, who knew that
this shrimp bambito's

00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:18,896
gonna become the head of the
entire Sanitation Commission?

00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:21,699
He could ruin me.

00:43:22,933 --> 00:43:24,802
I am this far
from sending his ass

00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:26,770
to the bottom
of a landfill.

00:43:26,904 --> 00:43:28,205
You'd do that to Rizzo?

00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:30,841
What do you think?

00:43:33,077 --> 00:43:35,713
If you didn't come home
with me, it's my only choice.

00:43:38,415 --> 00:43:40,184
Hey, hey, guys,
what's up, huh?

00:43:40,317 --> 00:43:42,753
I'm having a talk
with my brother here.

00:43:42,886 --> 00:43:44,421
BOBBY:
We've gotta go.

00:43:44,555 --> 00:43:47,024
Two weeks, Carmine. Okay?

00:43:47,157 --> 00:43:48,425
BOBBY:
Come on, I'm hungry.

00:43:48,559 --> 00:43:49,760
Okay, Frank.

00:43:49,893 --> 00:43:51,095
BOBBY:
Let's go. Come on.

00:43:51,228 --> 00:43:52,963
Let's go grab
a couple of omelets.

00:43:54,198 --> 00:43:55,966
See you, Carmine.
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:57,968
Come on, Frank, lighten up.

00:44:00,337 --> 00:44:02,473
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

00:44:05,743 --> 00:44:07,745
[CAR DRIVES OFF]

00:44:07,878 --> 00:44:08,746
I'm in.

00:44:08,879 --> 00:44:10,881
What?
I said, I'm in.

00:44:11,015 --> 00:44:13,951
That's great. Hold Rifka
while I get us a cocktail.

00:44:14,084 --> 00:44:15,285
Oh, Jesus Christ, Sam.

00:44:15,419 --> 00:44:17,021
Don't make any sudden moves.

00:44:18,122 --> 00:44:19,657
Now I can tell you
about the safe.

00:44:19,790 --> 00:44:21,525
What safe?
Harvey's safe.

00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:24,395
Sam, I'm not a thief.
Ha! Don't make me laugh.

00:44:24,528 --> 00:44:26,530
Harvey's trying
to cut you out of the will.

00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:29,033
Think about Max. You can't
put him through college

00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:30,167
selling mobile homes.

00:44:30,300 --> 00:44:31,602
Okay, okay, when?

00:44:31,735 --> 00:44:33,437
A week from tonight.

00:44:33,570 --> 00:44:35,939
That'll take his option
till the end of the month.

00:44:36,073 --> 00:44:37,107
[SNAKE TAIL RATTLES]

00:44:37,241 --> 00:44:39,209
Rifka's a rattlesnake.
Yeah, that's right.

00:44:39,343 --> 00:44:41,245
[SNAKE TAIL RATTLES]

00:44:41,378 --> 00:44:42,312
Please take him.

00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,582
He likes you.
Yeah.

00:44:49,086 --> 00:44:49,953
Hey, Lex.

00:44:50,087 --> 00:44:51,021
Hello, officer.

00:44:53,090 --> 00:44:54,758
Take good care
of these guys.

00:44:54,892 --> 00:44:56,694
Oh, yeah. Love them
and leave them.

00:44:57,928 --> 00:44:59,363
When do you go?

00:44:59,496 --> 00:45:00,798
I don't know.

00:45:00,931 --> 00:45:01,865
Soon, maybe.

00:45:03,067 --> 00:45:06,670
Yeah, well...
we'll miss you around here.

00:45:06,804 --> 00:45:09,206
There are few things
I'll miss about this place.

00:45:09,339 --> 00:45:10,774
Hope I'll be one of them.

00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:13,644
Oh, you will be.

00:45:18,182 --> 00:45:20,517
MAN [OVER PA]:
Ralph Ramsey,
you have a phone call.

00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:22,386
Ralph Ramsey, a phone call.

00:45:29,259 --> 00:45:31,562
Florida's not such a bad place.

00:45:31,695 --> 00:45:33,797
Compared to here,
it's a vacation wonderland.

00:45:33,931 --> 00:45:35,032
[CHUCKLES]

00:45:35,165 --> 00:45:37,034
I'm gonna be making
$100,000 a year,

00:45:37,167 --> 00:45:39,570
not including health benefits
or bonus packages.

00:45:39,703 --> 00:45:42,506
I'm not a window
or a real estate deal.

00:45:42,639 --> 00:45:45,309
A window doesn't have to be
a deal. You're you.

00:45:46,376 --> 00:45:47,244
I love you.

00:45:47,377 --> 00:45:48,645
Just like that?

00:45:48,779 --> 00:45:52,516
When it's open, it's open,
just like that.

00:45:55,719 --> 00:45:57,654
[CLICKING]

00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:05,295
Hi.
I'm the security guard.

00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:06,697
Can I help you?

00:46:06,830 --> 00:46:07,931
My family.

00:46:08,532 --> 00:46:09,967
My family.

00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:12,870
We're giving Harvey cash
for this Little Vegas deal.

00:46:14,071 --> 00:46:15,239
Uh...

00:46:15,372 --> 00:46:16,940
I'm supposed to check out
the safe,

00:46:17,074 --> 00:46:18,776
you know,
make sure it's acceptable.

00:46:20,544 --> 00:46:22,045
You keep all your dough
in there?

00:46:22,179 --> 00:46:23,046
Sure.

00:46:23,180 --> 00:46:24,782
It's our safe.

00:46:24,915 --> 00:46:26,550
Jesus H. Christ.

00:46:41,231 --> 00:46:42,166
Hey, Lexie.

00:46:45,335 --> 00:46:46,270
Excuse me.

00:47:01,084 --> 00:47:02,152
Goddamn it!

00:47:02,953 --> 00:47:03,854
[KNOCKING]

00:47:03,987 --> 00:47:05,889
Whatever you're selling,
get lost.

00:47:06,023 --> 00:47:08,559
I'll come back later.
Oh, I hate my life.

00:47:14,031 --> 00:47:16,133
Sorry about earlier.
Yeah, right.

00:47:16,266 --> 00:47:17,801
I wasn't expecting.
Steve--

00:47:17,935 --> 00:47:20,170
He seems like an
upbeat guy for a cop.

00:47:22,906 --> 00:47:24,208
He does accounting too.

00:47:25,976 --> 00:47:26,844
Accounting?

00:47:26,977 --> 00:47:28,078
[CHUCKLES]

00:47:28,212 --> 00:47:29,379
In Las Vegas?

00:47:29,513 --> 00:47:31,048
[LAUGHING]

00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:38,088
I know guys who've been
convicted for less than that.

00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:41,792
[♪♪♪]

00:47:53,070 --> 00:47:54,338
Oh! Oh, oh, oh!

00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:57,507
Max, right?
That's right.

00:47:58,976 --> 00:48:01,178
Your father dates Lexie?
Lexie?

00:48:02,045 --> 00:48:04,281
Uh... No. Don't think so.

00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:06,884
Where you headed?

00:48:07,017 --> 00:48:10,220
You know, usual place to do
my homework or something.

00:48:11,188 --> 00:48:12,289
[FORCED CHUCKLE]

00:48:12,422 --> 00:48:16,059
[BOTH CHUCKLE AWKWARDLY]

00:48:18,128 --> 00:48:19,730
How do you know
when the windows open?

00:48:19,863 --> 00:48:21,231
A guy like you
would just know.

00:48:21,365 --> 00:48:22,699
That's the beauty
of windows.

00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:24,902
You just know.

00:48:25,035 --> 00:48:26,737
If you can look
whoever it is in the eye,

00:48:26,870 --> 00:48:28,205
and at
the right moment,

00:48:28,338 --> 00:48:30,173
give a little bit
of yourself...

00:48:31,408 --> 00:48:33,010
you can sell 'em
the world.

00:48:35,445 --> 00:48:36,380
The world?

00:48:37,981 --> 00:48:38,916
The world.

00:48:41,785 --> 00:48:43,186
I gotta tell you
about windows.

00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:44,922
Forget about the windows.
Go to school.

00:48:45,055 --> 00:48:46,056
And learn what?

00:48:46,189 --> 00:48:47,891
Max,
it's time for homework.

00:48:48,025 --> 00:48:50,460
Homework? Are you kidding?
I've never done homework.

00:48:50,594 --> 00:48:52,262
There's a first time
for everything.

00:48:52,396 --> 00:48:55,365
Carmine.
Max, either you hit the books,

00:48:55,499 --> 00:48:56,733
or I'm gonna hit you.

00:48:56,867 --> 00:48:57,801
Capiche?

00:48:59,303 --> 00:49:00,237
Capiche.

00:49:04,308 --> 00:49:06,043
Carmine, relax.

00:49:06,176 --> 00:49:07,044
He'll be fine.

00:49:07,177 --> 00:49:08,345
I grew up
in this park,

00:49:08,478 --> 00:49:11,481
and Harvey used to be
a cheesy little weasel.

00:49:13,483 --> 00:49:15,619
Yeah, maybe you'd better
keep an eye on him.

00:49:17,587 --> 00:49:19,589
How did your mother
handle it?

00:49:19,723 --> 00:49:20,958
She drank like a fish.

00:49:22,559 --> 00:49:24,494
So I'll see you later?

00:49:24,628 --> 00:49:26,196
Yeah, that'd be nice.

00:49:26,330 --> 00:49:28,265
[♪♪♪]

00:49:32,169 --> 00:49:34,104
MARTHA:
I started drinking
when Saul left.

00:49:35,172 --> 00:49:36,306
CARMINE:
Why?

00:49:36,440 --> 00:49:38,408
